-- Nigeria prices 3-year govt bond at 12.14 pct to attract investors
-- By Oludare Mayowa
-- Fri Oct 17, 2014 06:40AM EDT
-- None



LAGOS, Oct 17 (Reuters) - Nigeria priced its 3-year government bond <NG3YT=RR> at 12.14 percent at its latest auction on Wednesday, up 102 basis points from the previous sale, to attract foreign investors unnerved by falling oil prices <LCOc1> and a weaker naira <NGN=D1> currency.

